modules.description: Returns the width and height of an image as floating-point values, and retrieves a transformation matrix used for rendering. Works with the `t` type, which represents image data structures. Used to extract geometric properties and transformation parameters for real-time graphics processing.

Creates and manages a rendering context for pixel-based graphics, supporting operations like setting pixel colors and clearing the screen. Works with a mutable internal buffer representing a grid of color values. Used to generate and manipulate raster images in real-time applications.

Parses SVG files into a structured representation and converts them into raster images. Works with SVG data, image buffers, and rendering contexts. Used to load and display vector graphics in OCaml applications with SDL2 integration.

Extracts geometric properties and transformation matrices from image data, while enabling real-time manipulation of pixel grids. It handles operations such as setting individual pixel colors, clearing buffers, and retrieving dimensions as floats. The module supports dynamic graphics processing by combining geometric data with mutable raster updates. Examples include rendering scalable vector graphics and adjusting visual elements on the fly.
